│ robust, I'll add a fallback in VPTransformState::get: if no vector exists and the specific lane scalar isn't available, but the first-lane scalar exists, return that scalar. This       │
│ mirrors uniform behavior and prevents the assertion while keeping semantics reasonable for cases where only a single scalar was materialized.                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '231,238{s/assert(hasVectorValue(Def));/if (!hasVectorValue(Def)) {\n    if (hasScalarValue(Def, Lane))\n      return Data.VPV2Scalars[Def][Lane.mapToCacheIndex(VF)];\n    if    │
│ (hasScalarValue(Def, VPLane::getFirstLane()))\n      return Data.VPV2Scalars[Def][0];\n  }\n  assert(hasVectorValue(Def));/}' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp                    │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
